{"id": "g3gcid", "title": "From Alpha to Omega", "selftext": "**TL;DR - observing for a long small caps, short big cap tech play/ pairs trade, somewhat market-neutral.**\n\nMuch has been made about value/growth recently. The NASDAQ 100 (proxy: $QQQ) is alpha.\n\n&#x200B;\n\n[Source: ZeroHedge](https://preview.redd.it/mocszl7hrht41.jpg?width=976&format=pjpg&auto=webp&s=7f9576122162c88722a4d4dfd30dfa0ff2d7508e)\n\n&#x200B;\n\n[QQQ to SPY ratio, 10 Years](https://preview.redd.it/vrap0aa5nht41.png?width=840&format=png&auto=webp&s=498774b5a4e95d70701b638ae2f2ed5450e7f08f)\n\n&#x200B;\n\nThe Russell 2000 (proxy: $IWM) is the Omega.\n\n[IWM to SPY ratio, 10 years](https://preview.redd.it/0ftbqxdjnht41.png?width=844&format=png&auto=webp&s=b60f4fe67473ad72648050861947dcc9204869cc)\n\n&#x200B;\n\nCombining the charts above, you get...\n\n[QQQ to IWM Ratio, 10 Years](https://preview.redd.it/wq59hbgwnht41.png?width=833&format=png&auto=webp&s=8332148499b812c797fb6ad3725d31e7710f1c6f)\n\n&#x200B;\n\n[QQQ to IWM Ratio, YTD](https://preview.redd.it/ytvrnucynht41.png?width=832&format=png&auto=webp&s=d850cdcab8eb4981e67c4c138514de7886ea3543)\n\n&#x200B;\n\nThe QQQ has outperformed IWM by 151% in 10 years. You do not get this sort of performance variance without flows...\n\n[QQQ and IWM flows YTD](https://preview.redd.it/tyz7ucr7oht41.png?width=1770&format=png&auto=webp&s=5dd85abae4a74a6cf69fddcf33b7bf821394f309)\n\n&#x200B;\n\nReversals don't happen because a magical technical level is reached, or the chart looks some inordinate way, but rather flows shift. The reason flows change is pointless in the end, but rather should be observed. **That said, below I'll provide my best guess on what I believe might provide a catalyst for a reversal of this trend. I'd also like to hear your thoughts as well.**\n\nIf one is inclined to make a trend reversal bet, option term structures give one an opportunity to take advantage of elevated premium, even when beta-adjusted, at 7-60 DTE in my view.\n\n[Source: iVolatility, ToS](https://preview.redd.it/km2inpfnoht41.png?width=510&format=png&auto=webp&s=4b706899e3324ae5b82d54538d1a9cdea0413386)\n\n&#x200B;\n\n**Thoughts on reversal possibilities**: I do not believe recent stimulus is going to \"cure\" the economic contraction. This is to say, the amount of stimulus currently provided will not be enough. I expect an infrastructure plan of some sort, additional fiscal stimulus to small and medium size businesses, and a continued (if not accelerated) protectionism posture. These factors are likely to support smaller companies, publicly traded or otherwise.", "created_utc": 1587178923.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/g3gcid/from_alpha_to_omega/", "is_self": true}